title: 19-year-old woman shot in the back in Parkland
content:
PARKLAND, Wash. -- A 19-year-old woman was seriously injured when she was shot in the back Thursday night.
Police say the shooting occurred as the woman was driving her car in the parking lot of the Monterra Apartments on 111th St. Ct. E. just before 10 p.m.
After the woman was wounded, she drove into a barrier. Medics arrived and took the woman to St. Joseph's Hospital where she was listed in serious condition.
Several other people were in the car at the time of the shooting, and police have arrested a 15-year-old boy. Everyone else who had been in the car ran away from the scene after the shooting, police said.
Police are still trying to track down the other witnesses.
